<span id="freeTextContainer15771057706983911181">A visionary account of American life--and the long-awaited sequel to one of the most celebrated novels of the past decade--<i>Independence Day</i> reveals a man and our country with unflinching comedy and the specter of hope and even permanence, all of which Richard Ford evokes with a keen intelligence, perfect emotional pitch, and a voice invested with absolute authority.</span>

