<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/814349-just-started-reading-this-pulitzer-prize">Just started reading this Pulitzer Prize winner and I&#39;m not that impressed. (Maybe it&#39;s because of the quality of other books on my current reading list.) Independence Day is top-heavy with details, some of it just a bit too much for this reader. Still, I&#39;ll stick with it. I did not read the other two book in Ford&#39;s trilogy. Am I being too critical?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_814349'><a id="like_count_community_question_814349" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/814349?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">5 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F12374.Independence_Day">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/814349-just-started-reading-this-pulitzer-prize">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/814349-just-started-reading-this-pulitzer-prize">See all 3 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

