<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/257468-good-goodreads-folk-this-question-is">Good Goodreads folk, this question is addressed to those who read Independence Day without reading the first book in the trilogy, The Sportswriter: Did you find it hard to follow? Did you thoroughly enjoy the book on its own merits? Or hate it on its own merits? All feedback welcome if it&#39;s pertinent to my main goal, which is to determine if people can jump in on the second book without being baffled. Thanks!</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_257468'><a id="like_count_community_question_257468" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/257468?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F12374.Independence_Day">like</a></span>

