<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/43165914-tom-wilkinson"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/43165914-tom-wilkinson">Tom Wilkinson</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I just finished it and never read the first book. Of course, I can&apos;t really know what I may have missed or not understood, but I never felt lost or ba<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I just finished it and never read the first book. Of course, I can't really know what I may have missed or not understood, but I never felt lost or baffled by starting with the second book. <br /><br />That said, I admire this book, but didn't love it. It has brilliant spots, huge ambition, and pithy insights galore, but really needed editing.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
